

String:-
A string is a sequence of characters. 
In java, objects of String are immutable which means a constant and cannot be changed once created.
for example:- "Hello World";
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
StringBuffer:-
StringBuffer class is a thread-safe and synchronized, mutable sequence of characters.
 A string buffer is like a String, but can be modified.
 
 For Example:-
 StringBuffer sbuffer = new StringBuffer("Hello");
 String s = new String(sbuffer); //Hello
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 StringBuilder:-
 StringBuilder class is a not a thread-safe & synchronized, mutable sequence of characters.
 A string builder is like a String, but can be modified. StringBuilder is  faster than stringBuffer
 For Example:-
 StringBuilder sbuilder = new StringBuilder("Masai");
String s = new String(sbuilder); //Masai
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
to String():-
he toString() method returns a string as a string.
It does not change the original string and  can be used to convert a string object into a string.

For Example:-
let text = "Hello World!";
let result = text.toString();//Hello World!

}